This paper deals with paraconsistent reasoning, which is a topic in logic and artificial intelligence. The use of quantified Boolean formulas suggests a connection to propositional logic and complexity theory, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the implementation of paraconsistent reasoning, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The analysis of complexity bounds and results suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
